	<text>
		<body>
			<div type="entry">
				<pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary02.jpg"/>
				<div>
					<dateline><date>Tuesday December 3rd 1861</date></dateline>
					<p xml:id="a1">We moved our <placeName>camp</placeName> from <placeName
							key="St. John’s College"
							ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_gazetteer.xml#linnpl080"
							>St. John’s College</placeName> to about a mile &amp; a half from
							<placeName key="Annapolis, MD"
							ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_gazetteer.xml#linnpl002"
							>Annapolis</placeName>. We are now comfortably fixed with the only
						disadvantage of a scarcity of <objectName type="food">water</objectName> — a
						very serious one by the way. <persName key="Jeremiah Miller"
							ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper048"
							>Jeremiah Miller,</persName> one of our <orgName>company</orgName>, died
						last night — about <time>eleven o’clock</time> — of hemorage of the lungs.
						We had hardly expected it, though we were about getting his discharge. We
						had a grave dug in the soldiers burying ground near <placeName
							key="Annapolis, MD"
							ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_gazetteer.xml#linnpl002"
							>Annapolis</placeName>. Our removal to-day prevented any discouraging
						effect which might have been were it not for the excitement caused by it.We
						are brigaded as [?] in the Second brigade of the Coast Division. <name
							type="weather">The day was bright and fine though somewhat cold.</name>
						One of the <objectName type="equipment">tents </objectName>caught fire &amp;
						burned up a while ago. We have given one of our <objectName
							type=" equpiment">wall-tents</objectName> to the servants, &amp; have
						taken a common <objectName type="equpiment">tent</objectName> for our
						kitchen &amp; <persName key="Dick Coulter"
							ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper025"
							>Dick’s quarters</persName>. We have a <objectName type="equipment"
							>sheet iron cook stove </objectName>&amp; one also for our <objectName
							type="equpiment">tent</objectName> which makes it cosy and comfortable.
						I was officer of the day yesterday. We received news of the death of
							<persName key="William Cameron"
							ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper083"
							>Will Cameron</persName> last Friday.</p>
				</div>
